  "info": {
    "name": "Birthday Messaging System API",
    "description": "A comprehensive API for managing users and their birthday messages with timezone-aware scheduling.\n\n## Features\n- User management (Create, Read, Update, Delete)\n- Timezone-aware birthday scheduling\n- Automatic birthday message delivery at 9 AM local time\n- Resilient email delivery with retry logic\n\n## Quick Start\n1. Set the `baseUrl` variable to your server URL (default: http://localhost:3000)\n2. Run the \"Health Check\" request to verify the server is running\n3. Create users with POST /api/user\n4. Manage users with GET, PUT, DELETE endpoints\n\n## Notes\n- All user endpoints are prefixed with `/api`\n- Timezone must be in IANA format (e.g., America/New_York)\n- Birthday format: YYYY-MM-DD\n- Email must be unique across all users",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "birthday-messaging-system",
    "version": "1.0.0"
  },
